Audio

     * [https://soundcloud.com/]SoundCloud - Audio hosting with an
       embeddable player. Up to 3 hours of content is free.
     * [https://www.mixcloud.com/]Mixcloud - Audio hosting with unlimited
       uploads and an embeddable player.
     * [https://www.spotify.com/]Spotify - You can embed any song, album,
       or playlist with a
       [https://developer.spotify.com/technologies/widgets/spotify-play-bu
       tton/]Spotify Play Button.

Books

     * [https://github.com/aharris88/google-bookshelves-widget]Google
       Books - Allows you to display the books in your Google Books
       Library.
     * [https://www.goodreads.com/api]Goodreads API and widgets - Allows
       you to access any of the Goodreads data. Widgets are found on the
       widgets tab on your [https://www.goodreads.com/user/edit]settings
       page.

Calendar and Scheduling

     * [http://calendar.google.com/]Google Calendar - Embeddable calendar
       that you can collaborate with other people.
     * [http://booking.timekit.io/]Booking.js - Beautiful embeddable
       booking widget.
     * [http://zenplanner.com/]zenplanner - Paid - Online scheduling for
       fitness.

Images

     * [https://www.flickr.com/]Flickr - Online photo hosting by Yahoo.

Maps

     * [http://maps.google.com/]Google Maps - Google maps are easily
       embeddable.
     * [https://www.mapbox.com/]Mapbox - Really nice looking embeddable
       maps.

Presentations

     * [https://prezi.com/]Prezi - Online presentations with really
       transitions that can zoom and rotate.
     * [http://lab.hakim.se/reveal-js/]Reveal.js - HTML presentation
       framework.
     * [http://slides.com/]Slides.com - A place for creating, presenting
       and sharing slide decks.
     * [https://speakerdeck.com/]SpeakerDeck - Upload your slides as a
       PDF, and get an online, shareable presentation.

Video

     * [https://www.youtube.com/]YouTube - Embeddable videos with
       unlimited uploads.
     * [https://vimeo.co/]Vimeo - Paid - Embeddable videos with no ads.
     * [http://www.vevo.com/]Vevo - Embeddable music videos.
     * [https://vine.co/]Vine - Embeddable vine videos.
     * [http://wistia.com/]Wistia - Free plan has a limit of 25 videos.

Code

     * [http://codepen.io/]Codepen - A playground of embeddable front-end
       code examples.
     * [http://jsbin.com/]JS Bin - Embeddable front-end code examples.
     * [http://jsfiddle.net/]JSFiddle - Embeddable front-end code
       examples.
     * [https://highlightjs.org/]highlight.js - Syntax highlighting for
       the web.

Functions as a Service

     * [https://1backend.com/]1Backend - Deploy your backend in seconds.
       Free tier included. Open source.
     * [https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/]AWS Lambda - AWS Lambda lets you
       run code without provisioning or managing servers. You pay only for
       the compute time you consume
     * [https://cloud.google.com/functions/]Google Cloud Functions -
       Create single-purpose, stand-alone functions that respond to Cloud
       events without the need to manage a server or runtime environment
     * [https://webtask.io/]Webtask by Auth0 - Call code on the server
       with simple HTTP, easier to set up by far than Lambda or Google's
     * [https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/services/functions/]Azure
       Functions - by Microsoft - same premise as Lambda on the Azure
       cloud
     * [https://www.iron.io/platform/ironworker/]IronWorkers - by Iron.io
       - Run code in a multilanguage containerized environment with
       unlimited scale and simple pricing
     * [http://open.iron.io/]IronFunctions - by Iron.io - IronFunctions is
       an open source serverless computing platform for any cloud -
       private, public, or hybrid.
     * [https://console.ng.bluemix.net/openwhisk/]OpenWhisk by IBM - part
       of their BlueMix hosting platform, and open source, ties into their
       Watson AI ecosystem nicely

Community

Comments

     * [https://github.com/eduardoboucas/staticman]Staticman - Staticman
       is a Node.js application that receives user-generated content and
       uploads it as data files to a GitHub repository. In practice, this
       allows you to have dynamic content (e.g. blog post comments) as
       part of a fully static website, as long as your site automatically
       deploys on every push to GitHub, as seen on GitHub Pages, Netlify
       and others.
     * [https://disqus.com/]Disqus - Easily embeddable comments with
       nested replies, multiple login methods, and email notifications.
     * [https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/comments]Facebook
       Comments - Embeddable comments for your site by Facebook.
     * [http://www.intensedebate.com/]IntenseDebate Comments - Embeddable
       comments with nested replies, multiple login methods, and email
       notifications.
     * [http://web.livefyre.com/apps/comments/]LiveFyre - Real-time
       comments, SEO-optimized, stocked with social features, and
       beautiful on both desktop and mobile.
     * [http://embed.redditjs.com/]Redditjs Embed Widget - Embed Reddit
       comments on your site. If it hasn't been posted, it will show a
       link to encourage the user to submit.
     * [https://muut.com/]Muut.com - Embeddable comments, forum and
       private messaging. A lot of functionality, but really low footprint
       left on your website.

Forms

Really Simple Forms

     * [http://formspree.io/]Formspree - Receive emails from a form on
       your static website.
     * [https://www.elformo.com/]elFormo - Simple form processing and
       response retrieval via email.
     * [http://flipmail.co/]Flipmail - Simple form processing and response
       retrieval via email.
     * [http://mailthis.to/]MailThis - Simple form submissions via email
       with optional attachments.
     * [https://getsimpleform.com/]Simple Form - Simple forms with
       optional file attachments, email notifications, and online
       submission viewing.
     * [https://github.com/stevensona/briskforms]Brisk Forms - Free form
       submission service emails you responses while keeping your email
       address private and is open source.
     * [https://www.99inbound.com/]99 Inbound - Form endpoint service with
       email/Slack notifications and third party app integrations (e.g.
       MailChimp)

Normal Forms

     * [https://www.google.com/forms/about/]Google Forms - Saves results
       into Google Sheets and can email you when there is a submission.
     * [https://formkeep.com/]FormKeep - Paid - View form submissions in a
       beautiful web interface. It has spam filtering and it integrates
       with webhooks such as Gmail, Trello, and Basecamp.
     * [http://www.123contactform.com/]123 Contact Form - Connects to
       other online services such at MailChimp, Salesforce, and Google
       Drive. It also integreates with payment Processers and includes
       security and analytics.
     * [http://www.formassembly.com/]FormAssembly
     * [https://www.formsite.com/]FormSite - Form buider, with payments,
       and form management.
     * [https://www.formstack.com/]FormStack - Forms with A/B testing,
       partial submission, analytics, and integrations.
     * [https://sheetsu.com/]Sheetsu - POST and GET your data to Google
       Spreadsheet.
     * [http://www.typeform.com/]Typeform - Awesome forms that can be
       embedded.
     * [http://www.wufoo.com/]Wufoo - Free or Paid - Forms that you can
       build with a form designer, with notifications, reports, and
       payments.
     * [https://www.zoho.com/crm/help/web-forms/set-up-web-forms.html]Zoho
       - Forms with file upload and captcha.
     * [https://help.github.com/articles/about-issues/]GitHub Issues -
       This is an interesting way for developers to get
       comments/questions. See
       [https://github.com/sindresorhus/ama]github.com/sindresorhus/ama
       for an example.
     * [https://github.com/utterance/utterances]Utterences - A lightweight
       comments widget built on GitHub issues.
     * [https://www.formbackend.com/]FormBackend - Create form-backends
       and submit your HTML forms to our backend. View the entries online
       and connect to other services. Receive an email every time a new
       entry is submitted.
     * [https://pageclip.co/]Pageclip - A flexible server / backend for
       HTML forms. View your data in the realtime web interface, or use
       the API to get CSV and JSON output.
     * [https://www.formester.com/]Formester - Forms and email marketing
       (lead collection, email campaigns, and newsletters) with
       integrations.

Provided by the Host

     * [https://www.netlify.com/docs/form-handling/]Netlify - Netlify
       comes with built-in form handling.

Live Chat

     * [https://www.jivochat.com/]jivochat - JivoSite is a professional
       live chat for websites that was specifically designed to increase
       your online sales.
     * [https://www.livechatinc.com/]LiveChat - Live chat on your website.
     * [https://www.olark.com/]Olark - Live chat on your website. You can
       also see who's on your website and what they're doing.
     * [https://snapengage.com/]SnapEngage - Live chat with integrations
       and custom styles.
     * [https://www.tawk.to/]tawk.co - Lets you monitor and chat with
       visitors on your website.
     * [https://www.websitealive.com/]WebsiteAlive - Live chat for your
       website & social networks.
     * [https://www.zopim.com/]Zopim - Live chat with free trial.

Newsletters

     * [http://mailchimp.com/]MailChimp - Free email marketing. You can
       pay to add more features.
     * [http://www.constantcontact.com/]Constant Contact - Email marketing
       with campaigns, autoresponders, and analytics.
     * [http://www.aweber.com/]AWeber - Email marketing with campaigns,
       autoresponders, and analytics.
     * [https://www.campaignmonitor.com/]Campaign Monitor - Email
       marketing with campaigns, autoresponders, and analytics.
     * [https://www.mailerlite.com/]MailerLite - Free email marketing. You
       can pay for more subscribers.

Social Media

     * [https://developers.google.com/+/web/embedded-post/]Google+ -
       Google+ embedded post.
     * [https://developers.pinterest.com/]Pinterest - Pin It Button.
     * [https://dev.twitter.com/web/embedded-tweets]Twitter - Embedded
       tweets.
     * [https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins]Facebook - Facebook
       embedded plugins.
     * [http://www.sharethis.com/]ShareThis - Sharing buttons for multiple
       social networks.
     * [https://www.kontaktify.com/]Kontaktify - A contact widget that
       provides an easy way for visitors to get in touch.

Surveys

     * [https://www.google.co.nz/forms/about/]Google Forms - You can use
       Google forms for surveys or for forms on your site.
     * [https://www.surveymonkey.com/]SurveyMonkey - Easy to use and free
       surveys.
     * [http://www.typeform.com/]Typeform - Really beautiful forms.
     * [https://qualaroo.com/]Qualaroo - Embed surveys anywhere on your
       website that comes up from the bottom right side of the screen.

E-Commerce

     * [https://www.ecwid.com/]Ecwid - Embeddable shopping cart.
     * [http://www.foxycart.com/]FoxyCart - Add a shopping cart with basic
       html code.
     * [https://snipcart.com/]SnipCart - Include a few lines of code for a
       full online shop.
     * [https://gumroad.com/]Gumroad - An all-in-one solution to sell your
       work.

Search

     * [http://lunrjs.com/]lunr.js - Simple full-text search in your
       browser.
     * [https://cse.google.com/cse/]Google Custom Search Engine - Search
       your site with a custom Google Search.
     * [https://www.algolia.com/]Algolia - Hosted Search API that delivers
       instant and relevant results from the first keystroke.

Analytics

     * [http://www.google.com/analytics/]Google Analytics - Free website
       analytics.

Other

     * [https://sketchfab.com/]Sketch Fab - Embeddable 3D content.

Related Lists

     * [https://github.com/b-long/awesome-static-hosting]Awesome Static
       Hosting
